content:
[9:41 PM] Eve: Hello, and welcome! I'm Eve, your AI assistant trained to help with psycho-oncology assessments. Regularly checking on your wellbeing is an important part of the healing process. Shall we get started?

[9:41 PM] Patient: My family has been very supportive during this difficult time

[9:41 PM] Eve: That's wonderful to hear that your family has been supportive. Having a strong support system can make a big difference. Now, could you tell me how you've been feeling about your treatment lately?

[9:41 PM] Patient: I'm managing the side effects okay so far

[9:41 PM] Eve: It's good to know that you're managing the side effects. Let's talk about your mood. How would you describe your mood over the past week?

[9:41 PM] Patient: I have good and bad days

[9:41 PM] Eve: It's completely normal to have ups and downs. Can you share what aspects of your cancer experience you find most challenging?

[9:41 PM] Patient: I worry about being a burden to my family

[9:41 PM] Eve: It's common to feel that way, but remember, your wellbeing is important to your family too. How confident do you feel in managing your physical symptoms and side effects?
